  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: stable\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X \"POST\" \"http://127.0.0.1:8545/\" \\\r\n     -H 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8' \\\r\n     -d $'{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": 0,\r\n  \"method\": \"erigon_getLogs\",\r\n  \"params\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"toBlock\": \"10174217\",\r\n      \"fromBlock\": \"10174215\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}'\r\n\r\n# diff\r\n\r\ncurl -X \"POST\" \"http://127.0.0.1:8545/\" \\\r\n     -H 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8' \\\r\n     -d $'{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": 0,\r\n  \"method\": \"eth_getLogs\",\r\n  \"params\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"toBlock\": \"10174217\",\r\n      \"fromBlock\": \"10174215\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}'\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nI usually use erigon_getLogs, Because the timestamp field is very easy to use. When the method is `erigon_getLogs`, the `transactionIndex` lose and always is 0x0.\r\n\r\n\r\nexample tx, the position is 187: https://etherscan.io/tx/0x1de7468f7aa545c10b011d16dde1c7322e3335a17964bf022621664bdc80a64e\r\n\r\n\r\nresult:  \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8017428/207594701-108fc2b3-f65b-4f3b-9a5d-2309d4084653.png)\r\n\r\n",
